1. Download and Install Windows Package Manager
2.Run This command on Powershell with administrator 
   #winget install Kubernetes.kind
3.Download and Install Docker Desktop 
4. Create a yaml file with name kind-config.yaml 

apiVersion: kind.x-k8s.io/v1alpha4
kind: Cluster
nodes:
- role: control-plane
  image: kindest/node:v1.24.1
- role: worker
  image: kindest/node:v1.24.1
- role: worker
  image: kindest/node:v1.24.1

5. Run Docker Desktop 
6. Go to the location where you have saved the kind-config.yaml 
7. Run this command
 #kind create cluster --config kind-config.yaml --name=multi-node

If You have followed this Steps Carefully Then Congratulation you have installed an created a cluster on your Local system
You can verify the cluster by running the following command

#kind get clusters

#kubectl get nodes 

